          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a manual (paddhati) for consultation by priest or priestly artisan for the purpose of drawing out a sacred diagram (maṇḍala) in a square shape. A number of Hindu and Vedic deities (such as Viṣṇu, Śiva, and Varuṇa) are evoked and installed in various sections of the diagram, typically during fire (homa) rites.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Sarvatobhadramaṇḍaladevatā</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti maṃḍaladevatāsamāptaḥ // (f. 5v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
